    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH1a0928-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:41:26.953+09:00">Heaven possesses light;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:41:51.98+09:00">it is not distressed by the darkness in which men live.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:42:06.213+09:00">Earth possesses riches;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:42:41.087+09:00">it is not distressed by the poverty in which men live.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:43:08.747+09:00">The sage possesses power,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:43:36.206+09:00">but he is not distressed by the peril in which men live.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:45:35.093+09:00">Though Heaven is not distressed by the darkness in which men live,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:44:38.86+09:00">yet by opening doors and parting windows, men may unfailingly draw from it their own light.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:45:16.848+09:00">It follows then that Heaven hs no tasks to attend to.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:48:28.051+09:00">3. Though Earth is not distressed by the poverty inwhich men live,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:49:09.519+09:00">yet, by felling trees and cutting grass, men may unfailingly draw from it their own wealth.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:49:39.607+09:00">It follows then that Earth has no tasks to attend do.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:50:06.048+09:00">4. Though the sage is not distressed by the peril in whihc men live,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:52:00.331+09:00">yet the people may, by being submissive to the sovereign and concordant in their subject status,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:53:59.103+09:00">unfailingly draw from him their own security. It follows then that the sage has no tasks to attend to.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:55:18.457+09:00">5. Thus when it is said that the Sage in his position as sovereign</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:55:57.081+09:00"> is able not to do men harm</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:56:04.561+09:00">but is unable to free men from harm of their own making,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:56:36.487+09:00">it implies that the people rid themselves of the things which cause them harm.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:58:38.433+09:00">is due to his having been given it</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:59:09.81+09:00">not to his having taken it;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:59:27.339+09:00">the proper relationship of the people to the Sage</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:58:33.013+09:00">6. That the sage possesses the world</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-18T23:59:44.499+09:00">is that they supply his necessities.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:00:27.212+09:00">not that they cause the Sage to supply their necessities.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:00:57.947+09:00">It follows then that the sage has no task to attend to.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:01:54.252+09:00">7. Though Mao Ch'iang and Xi Shih</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:02:02.559+09:00">were the most beautiful women in the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:02:31.149+09:00">if one were to dress them in [bear]-skin and demon-masks</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:02:58.273+09:00">everyone who saw them would run away;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:03:33.502+09:00">but if one were to have them change into fine black linen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:04:03.7+09:00">everyone who walked by them would stop in his tracks.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:04:53.263+09:00">8. So it can be seen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:05:35.356+09:00">that fine black linen is an aid to beauty.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:05:46.761+09:00">If the comely dispense with it,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:05:58.301+09:00">their beauty will be unpleasing.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:07:51.85+09:00">9. Carriers can make their way beyond the farthest valley</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:07:47.352+09:00">only because oth the ointment [they apply].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:07:59.904+09:00">and walk through the wilderness for thousands of miles,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:10:05.886+09:00">If carriers dispense with ointment,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:10:51.606+09:00">their feet will be ruined.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:11:20.766+09:00">10. Thus when it is said that</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:12:12.044+09:00">The Rearing Serpent sports in the mists,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:12:27.524+09:00">The Flying Dragon rides on the clouds,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:16:52.644+09:00">But when the clouds are gone and the mists have cleared, they are no different from earthworms.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:17:03.887+09:00">the point is that they have lost the vehicles on which they rode.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:58:16.472+09:00">11. Thus when men of excellence are oppressed by a worthless man</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:58:35.435+09:00">it means that their authority is not as weighty as his;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.51" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:58:59.186+09:00">when worthless men are subjected to a man of excellence,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.52" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T00:59:46.68+09:00">it means that his position is more exalted than theirs.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:00:17.83+09:00">As a simple yeoman, Yao</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.54" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:00:28.399+09:00">could not command his neighbors,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.55" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:00:43.523+09:00">but once he had faced South as King,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.56" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:01:33.851+09:00">then, "what he ordeed was done and what he fobade ceased to be done."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.57" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:02:10.987+09:00">13. From this it can be seen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.58" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:02:32.718+09:00">that excellence is not enough to bring worthlessness into subjection,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.59" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:03:07.504+09:00">but that circumstances and position are enough to bend excellence under oppression.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.60" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:03:41.793+09:00">14.  Thus, when a decisive role is played by a man of no repute,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.61" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:04:35.568+09:00">it is because his authority has weight;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.62" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:04:59.984+09:00">when a bolt flies high from a weak crossbow,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.63" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:05:30.044+09:00">is it because it is carried on the wind;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.64" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:05:45.713+09:00">when the orders of a person of no worth are carried out,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.65" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:06:00.048+09:00">it is because he received aid from many.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.66" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:06:56.999+09:00">15. Thus, one who carries heavy burdens and crosses high mountains</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.67" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:07:08.739+09:00">is not careless about the use of ointment;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.68" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:07:28.936+09:00">one who loves little children</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.69" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:07:44.988+09:00">is not careless about the choice of a nurse;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.70" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:08:02.709+09:00">one who travels on dangerous roads and journeys to distant places</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.71" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:08:26.868+09:00">is not careless aobut the choice of a driver.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.72" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:09:06.622+09:00">These are illustrations of the principle that "aid obtained means success;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.73" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:09:29.857+09:00">aid rejected means ruin.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.74" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:10:06.324+09:00">16. That the ower of the Three Kings and the Five Protectors</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.75" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:10:23.509+09:00">was of the same order as that of Heaven and Earth,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.76" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:10:44.722+09:00">that it had access to the world of demons and gods,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.77" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:11:01.206+09:00">and embraced all living things,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-1a.78" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:11:16.977+09:00">was due to the fact that they obtained aid from all.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:29:18.872+09:00">17.  In antiquity, the artisans did not perform more than one task</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:15:17.233+09:00">and the well-born did not hold more than one office..</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:17:44.866+09:00">Since the artisans did not perform more than one task, there tasks were lessened;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:18:12.501+09:00">and since their tasks were lessened, it was easy to master them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:19:14.2+09:00">Since the well-born did not hold more than one office,their duties were few;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:19:39.045+09:00">and since their duties were few, it was easy to discharge them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:20:07.906+09:00">Therefore it was possible for the positions of the well-born to be held a lifetime,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:20:44.58+09:00">and for the tasks of the artisans to conform to constant standards.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:21:36.172+09:00">18. "The sons of artisans have ability without having to learn."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:21:48.043+09:00">This does not mean that they are born with their skills;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:23:20.344+09:00">it refers to the fact that they perform tasks which  conform to constant standards.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:24:10.086+09:00">19. In these present times, the state is not guided by the constant Way</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:24:50.443+09:00">and his officials are not regulated by constant laws.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T01:25:26.844+09:00">This is why the state is daily enmeshed in greater error.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:04:32.078+09:00">the officials are unqualified [to practise them].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:06:28.897+09:00">When the officials are unqualified, the principles of the Way languish.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:07:30.918+09:00">Even where the doctrines [of the Way] are perfectly formulated,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:06:42.856+09:00">When the principles of the Way languish, the excellent and the wise are admired.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-2a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:11:28.875+09:00">When the excellent and the wise are admired, the most vital functions in the administration of the State are left to the discretion of a single man. 【Presumably because there is no way to select administrative personal with these admired qualifications other than by the private judgment of the ruler.】</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:12:19.851+09:00">21. In antiquity, the intent of [the injunction], "Establish the Son of Heaven and honor him,"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:26:38.619+09:00">that unless there was a single object of honor, without peer in the world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:11:58.028+09:00">was not to bring benefit to a single man.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:12:24.221+09:00">It meant rather</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:20:38.129+09:00">the principles [of the Way] would have no point of access [to the world].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:21:34.943+09:00">The access to the principles [of the Way] is for the sake of the whole world.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:22:56.925+09:00">Thus, it is the case that the Son of Heaven is established for the sake of the whole world,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:27:47.729+09:00">not that the whole world is established for the sake of the Son of Heaven;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:27:59.768+09:00">that the ruler of a state is established for the sake of the state,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:28:40.679+09:00">not that the state is established for the sake of the ruler;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:29:03.558+09:00">and that the incumbent of an office is established for the sake of the office,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:29:05.139+09:00">not that the office is established for the sake of the incumbent.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:31:25.08+09:00">Even though the laws are not good,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-3a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:34:50.909+09:00">they still are preferable to no laws at all.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:44:53.06+09:00">24. The reason people throw buckles and? apportion property,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:36:44.819+09:00">and throw whips to apportion horses,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:37:03.259+09:00">is not because buckles and whips give equal portions.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:40:09.59+09:00">They keep those who receive get the better portion from knowing whom they should be grateful to,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:40:56.668+09:00">and keep those who receive the worse portion from knowing whom they should be resentful of.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:43:52.715+09:00">These are means by which to prevent resentment and expectation from arising.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:45:53.212+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-4a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:48:17.695+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0928_CHANT_001-4a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2025-03-19T02:48:52.92+09:00">25. The discerning ruler never initiates tasks or apportions duties</seg>
                </p>
